1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,586
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:08,466
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,635
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,804
<i>♪ Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,141
<i>♪ One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:17,225
<i>♪ In the world's mess</i> ♪

7
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:19,060
[Cita] <i>Atoy, Queenie is missing.</i>

8
00:00:19,144 --> 00:00:21,020
<i>They need your help!</i>

9
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,522
[Atoy] <i>She didn't sleep here last night.</i>

10
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,149
Where could she have gone?

11
00:00:24,232 --> 00:00:27,485
[Rachel] <i>I know she only goes</i>
<i>to school and home. And Bayah Kayakap</i>

12
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:28,361
Bahay Kayakap?

13
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:31,281
[Dmitri] <i>We're all here</i>
<i>at Martina's event.</i>

14
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:32,741
[in English] <i>It's a shelter for women.</i>

15
00:00:33,324 --> 00:00:35,452
- [Audrey] <i>Where is he?</i>
- Who?

16
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:36,870
[Audrey] <i>I just thought I saw someone.</i>

17
00:00:36,953 --> 00:00:39,330
[Atoy] <i>The guy I fought with</i>
<i>at Endless Nights is here.</i>

18
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:41,041
[Karla] <i>What's he doing here?</i>

19
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:43,835
<i>Brother, could there be</i>
<i>an underground fight bar inside?</i>

20
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,170
[Atoy] <i>I don't know.</i>

21
00:00:45,253 --> 00:00:46,337
<i>But every time I see him,</i>

22
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,047
<i>something illegal seems to be happening.</i>

23
00:00:48,131 --> 00:00:50,717
[Peping] <i>But they told us maybe…</i>

24
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,844
Queenie eloped.

25
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:54,179
She wouldn't do that, Atoy.

26
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:57,265
[Atoy] <i>Jeff said she had a boyfriend.</i>

27
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:59,309
<i>She met him on a dating app.</i>

28
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:01,186
Maybe I'll make a profile on MatchTayo.

29
00:01:01,269 --> 00:01:02,437
Just to check if Queenie's there.

30
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,438
Don't!

31
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,649
[Atoy] <i>Just give me</i>
<i>all the names of the victims.</i>

32
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:07,650
<i>I'll handle it.</i>

33
00:01:07,734 --> 00:01:09,652
I'll find a way.

34
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,530
PREVIOUSLY

35
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:13,698
[song concludes]

36
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:14,616
<i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪

37
00:01:14,699 --> 00:01:16,826
I used to think, Emerson,

38
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:18,912
that you would get angry
at me if you saw me.

39
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,372
[sniffles]

40
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:24,751
But it hurts more knowing
that you've already forgotten me.

41
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,922
You've already forgotten me, Emerson.

42
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:30,215
‪[melancholic music playing]

43
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:34,636
[door clicks open]

44
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:35,970
[Cita] Tonet?

45
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:39,307
[melancholic music playing]

46
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,643
[Tonet] Ah, oh, Miss Cita.

47
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:42,811
Oh?

48
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:43,895
[Tonet chuckles softly]

49
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,481
[Cita] Why are you crying?

50
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:47,774
Oh, nothing.

51
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:51,986
Is it because Ame
teases you about Emerson?

52
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,488
[quirky sting]

53
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:59,994
Oh, well, there's nothing wrong
if you like him.

54
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:01,538
- Huh?
- [quirky sting]

55
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,082
Gross, Miss Cita.

56
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:04,999
[chuckles]

57
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:07,627
What's really the problem?

58
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,423
He is my brother.

59
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:15,426
‪-[dramatic sting]
‪-What? Good heavens!

60
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:19,973
Emerson is my older brother.

61
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:22,934
But we haven't seen
each other for a long time.

62
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,477
[nostalgic music playing]

63
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:26,938
That's why he doesn't
recognize me anymore.

64
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:32,235
Oh, why don't you introduce yourself?

65
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:33,361
Go to him.

66
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:36,281
I'm sure he misses you.

67
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:39,868
I don't think so.

68
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:41,661
He's been here a long time.

69
00:02:41,744 --> 00:02:44,164
Has he ever mentioned having a sibling?

70
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:48,501
Well, it's like…

71
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:52,505
No, because he's angry with me.

72
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:54,007
He's very angry with me

73
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:57,010
because I wronged him.

74
00:02:57,093 --> 00:03:00,346
Maybe he still hasn't forgiven me.

75
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:03,975
[soft grunt]

76
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,979
You know, Tonet?

77
00:03:08,062 --> 00:03:11,941
It's truly painful
when family members hurt each other.

78
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:16,946
But if you show him that you are
sincerely asking forgiveness,

79
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,616
and you've become a good person,

80
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:22,285
your brother won't be able to reject you.

81
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,924
[music fades]

82
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:37,926
[sauve theme music playing]

83
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,344
[motorcycle revving]

84
00:03:39,427 --> 00:03:41,262
[whirring]

85
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:43,264
[snipping]

86
00:03:45,808 --> 00:03:47,143
[sewing machine whirring]

87
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:48,645
[gun cocks]

88
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:50,521
[gunshots blasting]

89
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:54,901
[clicking]

90
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,987
[music intensifies]

91
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:06,704
[knocks on door]

92
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,710
[door clicks open]

93
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:15,463
[in English] Hi, Dad.

94
00:04:15,546 --> 00:04:16,464
[Dmitri] Hi.

95
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:21,219
I just wanted to tell you that, um…

96
00:04:21,302 --> 00:04:25,431
I already talked to Martina,
and I put her in her place.

97
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:29,560
[in English] Dad,
I can take care of myself.

98
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:32,939
Don't worry. I won't fight with her.

99
00:04:33,022 --> 00:04:34,399
- [in English] Okay?
- [in English] Yeah.

100
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:37,735
But if your relationship becomes toxic,

101
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:38,945
while we're all here,

102
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:42,907
you know, we can probably
go back to the States.

103
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:45,451
Anyway, my business here is done.

104
00:04:45,535 --> 00:04:47,120
Draco is back with us.

105
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:48,913
[unsettling music playing]

106
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:50,540
[in English] I don't think I'm…

107
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,417
ready to go back just yet.

108
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:56,087
[in English] Is this because…

109
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,922
of the man from your past?

110
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:01,009
[in English] I'll think about
what you said.

111
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:02,010
[in English] Okay?

112
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:04,470
[in English] I just want to rest, for now.

113
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:06,639
[in English] Good night, Dad.

114
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:09,600
[in English] Yeah.

115
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:10,768
[in English] Good night.

116
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:11,686
‪[music fades]

117
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:19,360
[suspicious music playing]

118
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:32,332
[in English] Mr. Regalia, I have here
the results of Ms. Audrey's tests.

119
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:34,959
[in English] Anything
we should be worried about?

120
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:38,171
Congratulations, sir,
you're going to be a grandfather,

121
00:05:38,254 --> 00:05:40,089
and you'll be an uncle.

122
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,550
[sinister music playing]

123
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:43,843
[in English] What?

124
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:46,220
Your daughter is around
five months pregnant.

125
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:49,474
This explains the physical changes
in her body.

126
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:51,517
Audrey is pregnant?

127
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:53,186
But, Doc…

128
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:58,274
Is it safe for her, and her baby,
with her condition?

129
00:05:58,357 --> 00:06:01,486
[in English] Well, we need to monitor
her pregnancy closely,

130
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:04,655
and there are some things
I'd like to discuss with you.

131
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:07,825
- Let's do that later, Doc. Thank you.
- [in English] Excuse me.

132
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:10,661
[music intensifies]

133
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:14,207
It looks like Audrey
had a boyfriend on the island.

134
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:18,711
[in English] Who could be the father
of Audrey's child?

135
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:22,006
The question is, do you want
to continue the pregnancy?

136
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:24,425
[in English] Or should we
just terminate it?

137
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:28,805
[music intensifies]

138
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:34,852
[music fades]

139
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:39,190
Martina already spoke to the orphanage
that will take the child.

140
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:41,025
[pensive music playing]

141
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:42,443
[Red, in English] Don't worry.

142
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,362
[in English] They cannot
trace it back to us.

143
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:47,406
[in English] Are we really
doing this to Audrey?

144
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:49,992
It's still her child.

145
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:54,288
My grandchild! Your niece!

146
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:58,417
Dad, we don't even know
who got her pregnant.

147
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:01,003
For all we know,
she hooked up with someone else,

148
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,421
then got pregnant. That's it!

149
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:05,258
[in English] Don't talk
about your sister that way!

150
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:07,093
[in English] Dad, Dad. Dad.

151
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:10,763
Red and I are just thinking
what would happen if Audrey woke up

152
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:12,140
and she has a child.

153
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:14,851
What if she looks for the father?

154
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,020
We might lose her forever.

155
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:20,022
[in English] You lose her forever.

156
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:23,693
[unsettling music playing]

157
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:25,820
We should continue with our plan,

158
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,281
the one we had before
we knew she was pregnant.

159
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,199
You should bring her to the US,

160
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,034
get her treated while she's in a coma,

161
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:35,538
then, when she wakes up,
therapy continues.

162
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:39,083
You'll rebuild your relationship.

163
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:42,003
[in English] All will be well.
But that can only happen

164
00:07:42,086 --> 00:07:45,756
if she's free
from distractions and responsibilities.

165
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:47,842
[music fades]

166
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:51,471
[tense music playing]

167
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,640
[Red] Martina and I will handle it.

168
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,059
So you won't have to worry.

169
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:22,585
- [baby cooing]
- [music intensifies]

170
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:25,505
[baby crying]

171
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:27,924
[music fades]

172
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:33,346
[tense music playing]

173
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,108
You know…

174
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:49,278
I really can't stand that woman anymore.

175
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:52,073
[in English] I need her out of here.

176
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:55,576
- [sighs]
- Didn't you hear what she said?

177
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:59,413
She even plans to meddle
in the company, right?

178
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,832
I don't know if she's just provoking us.

179
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,876
[in English] But I won't let her.

180
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:07,129
Why don't they just go back to the US?

181
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:11,175
Our setup was perfect then, Red.

182
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:15,388
We can move the way we want
because they weren't here.

183
00:09:15,471 --> 00:09:17,682
[in English] We even sacrificed
that damn baby to get to this point.

184
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:20,351
[in English] And now Audrey
is here to ruin everything?

185
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:22,436
And she claims she'll watch over things,

186
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,480
like she's so good and perfect!

187
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:28,609
I mean, what kind of girl
gets pregnant by a man

188
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,361
whose name she doesn't even know?

189
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:32,238
[in English] It doesn't make sense.

190
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:36,200
I feel like that mystery guy
is the reason she won't leave.

191
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:38,536
Exactly. What if they see each
other again?

192
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:40,621
And then they figure out
they have a child.

193
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,039
[in English] What then?

194
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:44,875
- [in English] Impossible.
- [in English] No.

195
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:46,711
There's social media now.

196
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:49,213
[in English] You can find anyone
and everyone there.

197
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:50,339
How would she know?

198
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:52,216
She doesn't even know his name, right?

199
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,343
[pensive music playing]

200
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:58,639
You know what? Don't worry about Audrey.

201
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,391
The time will come that she'll get tired,

202
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:01,892
and she will realize that… [inhales]

203
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,978
…what she's doing is pointless.

204
00:10:04,061 --> 00:10:05,396
By then…

205
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:10,860
we'll be the ones to push her
and Dad to go back to the US.

206
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:14,822
[in English] Relax.

207
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:16,032
[in English] Okay.

208
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:28,336
[music fades]

209
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:30,254
[birds and crickets chirping]

210
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:31,589
‪[footsteps approaching]

211
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:35,217
Ma'am, Sir Gavin said
he'll join you for breakfast.

212
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:38,304
Good. So I'll have someone to eat with.

213
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:39,722
‪[footsteps approaching]

214
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,518
[utensils clattering]

215
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:47,104
[mysterious music playing]

216
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:51,442
What are those… on your necklace?

217
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:54,487
Um, this, ma'am? It's a scapular.

218
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,699
And the other one?

219
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,332
Is that Saint Anthony?

220
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:07,708
[maid 1] Yes, ma'am.

221
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,378
[Audrey] Can I see it, please?

222
00:11:11,128 --> 00:11:12,254
It's beautiful.

223
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:15,132
Where did you get this?

224
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,968
Oh, from the church
of the miraculous saint, ma'am.

225
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,846
The image of Saint Anthony
was missing before, then returned.

226
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:24,016
And since then, everything and everyone
missing in their barangay

227
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,851
had been found.

228
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:29,021
[dramatic sting,
sentimental music playing]

229
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:32,274
[in English] Well, he is
the patron saint of lost things.

230
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:33,859
Yes, ma'am.

231
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:41,409
Um, which church is this?

232
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:44,161
In Barangay Tabang Lupa, Baclaran.

233
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,788
Are you going?

234
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:47,790
Did you lose something?

235
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,167
[Gavin, in English] I'll take you.

236
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,795
- Really?
- [in English] Yeah.

237
00:11:53,295 --> 00:11:55,631
We play ball with my friends in that area.

238
00:11:55,714 --> 00:11:57,174
[in English] So, I know the place.

239
00:11:57,758 --> 00:11:58,968
[in English] Okay.

240
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:04,265
[music intensifies]

241
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:09,979
[music fades]

242
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:15,109
Why do you play in this place?

243
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,945
[in English] Better basketball courts?

244
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:19,864
[in English] Let me guess.

245
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:22,032
Prettier girls, right?

246
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:24,243
Just one girl!

247
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:26,871
- Hmm.
- [in English] I only have eyes for one.

248
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:31,417
[in English] And, yes, she's…
She's always around here.

249
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,918
That explains it.

250
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,045
[gentle music playing]

251
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,507
You, Auntie, what are you praying for?

252
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,553
[in English] Closure, I guess.

253
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:46,724
It feels like I'm getting
mixed signals from the universe.

254
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:48,976
[in English] I just want closure
once and for all.

255
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,692
- [phone rings]
- Oh!

256
00:12:58,777 --> 00:13:00,571
Uh, Auntie, excuse me.

257
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:02,573
- I'll just answer my friend's call.
- Yes, go ahead.

258
00:13:02,656 --> 00:13:03,574
[phone clicks]

259
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:04,992
[Gavin] Hello?

260
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:08,287
[pensive music playing]

261
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:09,455
[soft chuckle]

262
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,672
I believe…

263
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:23,385
you are the one who can give me
the answer I'm looking for.

264
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:29,683
If it's really meant to be…

265
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:36,190
you'll find a way for us to meet again.

266
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:50,454
[music fades]

267
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:54,124
I spoke with a friend
of another missing girl.

268
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:57,628
We'll see if there are similarities

269
00:13:57,711 --> 00:14:00,047
with Queenie's case, Father.

270
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:03,175
If there are, it will surely help us.

271
00:14:03,717 --> 00:14:05,511
The police still have no news.

272
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:09,974
Oh, Atoy, I pray to Saint Anthony
almost every day

273
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,976
that Queenie will be
returned to us safely!

274
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,602
It will happen, Father.

275
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:15,354
- It will happen.
- I can hardly eat.

276
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:16,272
I can't sleep!

277
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,815
I keep thinking of her.

278
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:19,525
Oh. What happened to that child?

279
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:21,068
Father, don't worry. It will happen.

280
00:14:21,151 --> 00:14:24,655
I won't stop until she's back with you.

281
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:28,158
[Peping] I'll get sick from this,
with what's happening…

282
00:14:28,742 --> 00:14:30,160
I don't know what's with that child.

283
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:33,581
[epic music playing]

284
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:41,463
[pensive music playing]

285
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:48,387
Really.

286
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:49,305
[sobs]

287
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:50,806
Atoy, uh…

288
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:52,892
- Help me.
- Father, Father, just a moment.

289
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,685
- Excuse me.
- Oh, wh-where are you going…

290
00:14:54,768 --> 00:14:55,853
Atoy! [gasps]

291
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:58,355
[invigorating music playing]

292
00:14:58,439 --> 00:14:59,523
[Peping gasps]

293
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:12,077
Elaine!

294
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:18,667
[Atoy] Elaine!

295
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:23,380
[dramatic sting]

296
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:25,424
[music fades]

297
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:27,968
[Atoy] Elaine?

298
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:32,056
[pensive music playing]

299
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:33,057
[Atoy] Elaine.

300
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,225
Elaine, why didn't you show up at--

301
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:37,478
Oh. Sorry, miss.

302
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:40,314
Forgive me. I thought…

303
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:41,565
I thought…

304
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:45,277
[somber music playing]

305
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:53,243
[music intensifies]

306
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:03,003
Auntie, are you sure you're okay now?

307
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:05,339
Jason invited me out last minute.

308
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:08,008
[in English] Go. Be with your friends.

309
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,635
I can go home alone.

310
00:16:09,718 --> 00:16:12,846
[in English] Well, I hope you get
what you prayed for, Auntie.

311
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:15,474
I hope so.

312
00:16:15,557 --> 00:16:19,103
And good luck with the girls
you'll be courting.

313
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:21,230
Girls?! None, ah! What girls?

314
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,357
You can't fool me, Gavin.

315
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,525
There's really no one!

316
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:25,693
[in English] But are you sure you're okay?

317
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:27,403
- [in English] Promise?
- Go on. Go now.

318
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,488
[in English] Okay. I'll go ahead.
Drive safe!

319
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:31,448
- [in English] Bye. Have fun!
- [Gavin, in English] Yes!

320
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:36,787
[gentle music playing]

321
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,708
[girl] Since freshman year,

322
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,710
Mandy and I were roommates.

323
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,461
So we became friends.

324
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:46,630
Her parents are in the UK,

325
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:49,341
busy with their careers.

326
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:52,177
They rarely talk.

327
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,722
But I know the plan was for Mandy

328
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,807
to follow them to the UK
after she graduated.

329
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,518
But then…

330
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:01,437
She's been missing for a month?

331
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:04,189
Her parents came back to the Philippines,

332
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:08,485
but had to return quickly
to the UK for work.

333
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:12,781
Actually, Mandy's style
of dress suddenly changed.

334
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:15,868
I was surprised too, because…

335
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:17,661
Mandy was a soft girl.

336
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,663
Wasn't anyone influencing her?

337
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:20,581
[suspicious music playing]

338
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:26,587
Did she meet someone new or…

339
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,047
become friends with someone?

340
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:31,300
You're also thinking
Mandy eloped, aren't you?

341
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,302
No, no, no.

342
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,679
No, I don't think that about your friend.

343
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,890
Promise, I don't think that about her.

344
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,017
I'm just asking.

345
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:44,021
I'm checking the similarities
with Queenie.

346
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:48,025
Queenie met someone.

347
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,152
Became her friend.

348
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:54,907
She even dated him
through a dating app, MatchTayo.

349
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,075
Do you know that?

350
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:59,912
Actually, Mandy also had MatchTayo.

351
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:03,332
She kept her identity secret there.

352
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:08,629
She told me she was going
to meet a guy at a bar.

353
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:11,882
But she didn't tell me which one.

354
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:14,176
And after that…

355
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,178
nothing.

356
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,471
She never came home.

357
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:20,015
[music intensifies]

358
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:21,475
[energetic music playing]

359
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,770
I don't want to go to that bar!

360
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:26,647
It's too early!

361
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:29,024
It's a restobar. That's why it's open!

362
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:30,692
Come on!

363
00:18:30,776 --> 00:18:32,444
There's not much work at the shop!

364
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:38,117
And I want to see the inside,
because many bands play there.

365
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,119
Famous bands!

366
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:42,496
Perfect timing. Gavin invited us.

367
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:45,124
[quirky music playing]

368
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:48,710
You know, I've noticed
something about Gavin.

369
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:50,337
What?

370
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:53,966
He's always hanging around here.

371
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:56,635
And now he's inviting you to a bar.

372
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:57,553
He likes you.

373
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:01,140
- Likes? What do you mean likes?
- Likes!

374
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,267
Crush, that's it! He wants to court you!

375
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,268
No way!

376
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:05,185
Impossible.

377
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:07,229
[pensive music playing]

378
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:08,480
Oh?

379
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,232
Hmm, why are you blushing?

380
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:11,984
- What blushing?!
- Hmm.

381
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,902
So, you like Gavin too?

382
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:15,737
Then why don't you two just go out?

383
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:16,655
Go on a date together?

384
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:17,573
- Hey, don't say that!
- Why should I come along?

385
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:20,701
Don't say that! We're not leaving
each other, Tonet!

386
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:22,703
[music fades]

387
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:29,126
[bustling indistinct chattering]

388
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:36,675
[Karla] Too bad.

389
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:39,720
No band yet. It's still early.

390
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:41,221
[in English] Next time.

391
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:42,347
[teases]

392
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:44,266
Wow! So, there's a next date for you two.

393
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:46,310
Shut up!

394
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:47,519
[in English] Sorry.

395
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:51,023
[bustling indistinct chattering]

396
00:19:51,106 --> 00:19:53,525
- OMG, sis!
- What?

397
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:55,944
- It's Raki!
- Who's that?

398
00:19:56,528 --> 00:19:57,696
[Karla] You don't know?

399
00:19:57,779 --> 00:19:58,697
- Huh?
- Huh?

400
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:01,366
The vocalist of Munting Sigaw!

401
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,243
That band!

402
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:05,370
That's him, look!

403
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:08,123
Sis, he's so handsome!

404
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,791
That's him, look!

405
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,712
- [Karla] Hey, sis! Sis!
- [Tonet] Oh, he's coming over.

406
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:15,255
Hi. I'm Raki.

407
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:17,925
Hello!

408
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:22,054
[energetic rock music playing]

409
00:20:27,601 --> 00:20:28,810
Hey!

410
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:31,188
He's so handsome, sis!

411
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:33,273
- Huh?
- [scoffs]

412
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:37,653
Sis, I feel like I'm drowning!

413
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:40,030
- That's it?
- I met him, finally!

414
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:41,240
He's my idol!

415
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:43,784
You're too giddy over that Raki.

416
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,285
Well, of course!

417
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:48,413
I listen to their music,
then suddenly I meet the vocalist!

418
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:51,041
You do know band guys
are womanizers, right?

419
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:52,960
You have so much to say.

420
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:56,171
Can't I just be excited
because I met someone famous?!

421
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,547
You're overreacting!

422
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,383
Okay.

423
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:00,592
[upbeat music playing]

424
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,387
I'll step aside. Maybe…

425
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,055
- [Karla] Huh?!
- I might just disturb you.

426
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:06,765
- [Karla] Stay here.
- Shh. Go on.

427
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:08,767
This is your moment! Behave.

428
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:09,851
Sit.

429
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:10,894
[nervous chuckling]

430
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:13,438
[in English] Drinks? Coffee, tea, me?

431
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:14,481
[giggling] Just kidding.

432
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,774
You got this.

433
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:23,699
[music fades]

434
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:28,829
Sir, three of your best-selling
non-alcoholic drinks, please.

435
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:29,913
Okay.

436
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:36,420
[indistinct chattering]

437
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:40,173
Mmm, how often do you come here?

438
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:42,801
Ah, not really, sir.

439
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,512
Don't call me "sir".

440
00:21:45,595 --> 00:21:47,597
[in English] What kind
of music do you like?

441
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:50,017
[Tonet] Uh, me?

442
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,727
Uh, I'm not really into music.

443
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:55,188
Are you sure? Not even one?

444
00:21:57,607 --> 00:22:03,697
Actually, I have one favorite…
"Ili-Ili Tulog Anay".

445
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:06,450
Because my brother used to sing it

446
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:08,118
when we were kids.

447
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:11,621
Ma'am, here are your two drinks first.

448
00:22:12,456 --> 00:22:14,249
Can I hear your favorite song?

449
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,584
[Tonet] Sorry, I'll go ahead.

450
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:23,008
[suspicious music playing]

451
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:31,183
[laptop keys clicking]

452
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:35,437
Why do you have a laptop?

453
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,606
- Hmm?
- Are you going to play games?

454
00:22:38,231 --> 00:22:39,775
[in English] Games?

455
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:42,277
All you think about are games.

456
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,112
That's all that's in your head.

457
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:47,199
I don't really have anything to do here.

458
00:22:47,866 --> 00:22:49,242
[Atoy] Is that so?

459
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:52,204
Hmm. [clears throat]

460
00:22:53,371 --> 00:22:55,082
Do you want something to do?

461
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:56,750
Here.

462
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,962
- What's that?
- Read these names one by one.

463
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,466
[Atoy] Hmm?

464
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:06,968
[Atoy] What's the first?

465
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:09,805
‪[mysterious music playing]

466
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,098
Hmm?

467
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:14,976
Um, whose names are these?

468
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:16,645
[Atoy] Names of victims.

469
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:19,064
Names of missing women.

470
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:22,776
What I'll do is,
after you read me the names,

471
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:25,237
I'll look up their social media accounts.

472
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:28,240
I'll check what similarities they have.

473
00:23:28,323 --> 00:23:30,367
Why they became victims.

474
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:31,743
So, what do you say?

475
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,997
Ah, I don't want to read them anymore.

476
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:37,666
Why not?

477
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,962
It gives me chills.

478
00:23:42,045 --> 00:23:44,005
"Chills".

479
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:46,508
Ah, all right. Good luck with that then.

480
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:48,009
You're creeped out?

481
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:51,263
Hey, you're just making excuses
because you don't want to read, right?

482
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:54,516
[sinister music playing]

483
00:23:55,517 --> 00:24:00,522
[music intensifies]

484
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:10,073
[intense music playing]

485
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:20,834
[tense music playing]

486
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:26,381
[Paldo] <i>I can't accept it.</i>

487
00:24:26,464 --> 00:24:28,550
What did Tonet see in Emerson?
I'm more handsome than him.

488
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:30,135
If you're jealous, close your eyes!

489
00:24:30,218 --> 00:24:32,095
I was going to confess something to you.

490
00:24:32,179 --> 00:24:34,431
[Cita] Maybe you can check on Tonet there?

491
00:24:34,514 --> 00:24:36,433
They said Emerson is furious.

492
00:24:36,516 --> 00:24:37,934
[Emerson] Get out of here!

493
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:40,103
- [Emerson] Leave!
- [Cita] Emerson!

494
00:24:40,187 --> 00:24:41,438
[Atoy] You could talk this out properly.

495
00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:42,480
You're always acting superior!

496
00:24:42,564 --> 00:24:44,149
You deserve to have your face smashed!

497
00:24:44,232 --> 00:24:45,984
- [clamoring]
- [Cita] Hey! Stop!

498
00:24:46,067 --> 00:24:47,402
UP NEXT

499
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,946
I always check on that child.

500
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:52,282
But she never mentioned any problem to me.

501
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:53,658
Doesn't she talk to anyone else?

502
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:55,619
Lately, she's always on her laptop.

503
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,787
Friday, that was the last day
before she disappeared.

504
00:24:58,371 --> 00:25:00,207
Here, here. This is the last person
she talked to.

505
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:02,667
[in English] Hey! I know you!

506
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:03,710
Are you alone?

507
00:25:03,793 --> 00:25:05,128
I have a table there. Come on.

508
00:25:05,212 --> 00:25:07,214
Raki. Raki Roman.

509
00:25:07,297 --> 00:25:08,256
["Tailor" playing]

510
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:10,133
<i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

511
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,927
<i>♪ Holding the scissors</i> ♪

512
00:25:12,010 --> 00:25:13,929
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
